        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 5:13AM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 512 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Goode, or near Forest, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lynchburg...
Concord...
Forest...
Evington...
Rustburg...
Goode...
and Timberlake.
</description>
        <instruction>Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways. Drivers are urged to slow down and use
extra caution to avoid hydroplaning.</instruction>
